not destroy pre-existing DNA.

29:00.913 --> 29:02.697
- Do you know
if any other clothing

29:02.741 --> 29:04.090
was in the washing machine

29:04.133 --> 29:05.526
along with people's
exhibit number one?

29:05.569 --> 29:08.181
- Yes, I believe
it contained garments

29:08.224 --> 29:09.791
belonging to each
of the family members.

29:09.835 --> 29:12.446
- In your professional opinion,
Mr. Fitzsimmons,

29:12.489 --> 29:14.709
is it possible
that the defendant's DNA

29:14.753 --> 29:18.669
could have been transferred
during a wash cycle

29:18.713 --> 29:20.410
to his son's underwear?

29:20.454 --> 29:23.413
- Yes, tests have shown
that's possible.

29:23.457 --> 29:24.719
- Possible.

29:24.763 --> 29:25.938
How about likely?

29:25.981 --> 29:28.201
- Under certain conditions.

29:29.855 --> 29:31.770
- Thank you.

29:34.947 --> 29:36.905
- The people call Molly Conway.

29:36.949 --> 29:38.820
- Objection,
spousal privilege.

29:38.864 --> 29:40.996
- We'll take a recess.

29:41.040 --> 29:44.391
