she's being released.

30:37.792 --> 30:41.274
- Aside from being in a cast
for the next three months?

30:46.148 --> 30:47.584
You know, Fin,
I'm a mom and a cop.

30:47.628 --> 30:49.064
That's it.
That's who I am.

30:49.108 --> 30:50.631
- That's more than most.

30:50.674 --> 30:54.200
- And what happens
when I wake up in the morning

30:54.243 --> 30:55.897
and I can't do
one of those things?

30:55.941 --> 30:57.333
Does that make me

30:57.377 --> 30:59.248
half the person that
I was the night before?

30:59.292 --> 31:01.120
- Well, excuse me
for being redundant,

31:01.163 --> 31:02.469
but you're still
more than most.

31:02.512 --> 31:04.471
- That's very nice
of you to say.

31:04.514 --> 31:08.954
But the fact of the matter is,
the truth is,

31:08.997 --> 31:11.695
I got winded.

31:11.739 --> 31:14.829
I was chasing that Conway kid
and I--

31:14.873 --> 31:16.918
I had to stop.

31:16.962 --> 31:18.789
And now an innocent woman
who was riding her bike

31:18.833 --> 31:22.576
has a broken leg because of--
because of me.

31:22.619 --> 31:24.621
- And no matter how much
you sucked for air,

31:24.665 --> 31:25.840
you couldn't
fill your lungs.

31:25.884 --> 31:27.102
- That's right.

31:27.146 --> 31:29.017
- And your legs
felt like lead.

31:29.061 --> 31:30.323
- Bingo.

31:30.366 --> 31:32.281
- Welcome to the club.

31:32.325 --> 31:36.198
Liv, no one expects you
to be Wonder Woman.

31:36.242 --> 31:38.157
- I do.

31:38.200 --> 31:40.420
- Yeah, well, and I used
to think I was Superman.

31:41.812 --> 31:44.293
- Life.

31:45.251 --> 31:48.645
Time.

31:48.689 --> 31:51.344
I mean,
what you gonna do?

32:01.920 --> 32:06.141
♪

32:09.449 --> 32:11.277
- Help yourself.
- I thought you only drank beer

32:11.320 --> 32:13.192
during a trial.
- Well, this one's

32:13.235 --> 32:14.758
basically over.
- You had to know

32:14.802 --> 32:16.064
that judge
wasn't going to let a wife

32:16.108 --> 32:18.371
testify against her husband.

32:18.414 --> 32:20.721
- I never underestimate the
bias or ignorance of judges.

32:20.764 --> 32:23.332
- And we had to get an honest
and intelligent one.

32:26.248 --> 32:28.163
Want to tell me
about Sam?

32:28.207 --> 32:29.686
- Well, he's terrified
of his old man

32:29.730 --> 32:31.427
and he's embarrassed by him.

32:31.471 --> 32:33.516
- It's par for the course.

32:33.560 --> 32:35.736
- Tell me about it.

32:38.304 --> 32:39.696
- You know, if I can
get Sam on the stand

32:39.740 --> 32:41.350
and talk to him man-to-man--

32:41.394 --> 32:42.656
- Yeah, but without
his mother's testimony,

32:42.699 --> 32:45.006
Karey's got no reason
to call him.

32:45.050 --> 32:46.616
That ship has sailed.

32:49.880 --> 32:52.883
- Maybe I can grab the line
before it's too far from shore.

32:59.238 --> 33:01.588
- Nah, I got this one.
Go home.

33:02.763 --> 33:05.418
How much is this gonna hurt me?

33:09.378 --> 33:11.772
How long has he been here?

33:18.779 --> 33:18.997
.

33:19.040 --> 33:20.520
- The people call Molly Conway.

33:22.217 --> 33:24.915
Did someone hit the replay
button when I wasn't looking?

33:30.878 --> 33:32.836
- I'm too young
for a senior moment.

33:32.880 --> 33:35.013
I know I ruled
on this yesterday, Mr. Stone.

33:35.056 --> 33:37.276
- Circumstances have changed,
Your Honor.

33:37.319 --> 33:39.017
- What, they got
a quickie divorce?

33:39.060 --> 33:40.975
Not that it would matter.

33:41.019 --> 33:42.672
- Because Mrs. Conway
tampered with evidence

33:42.716 --> 33:44.326
and misled the police,

33:44.370 --> 33:46.850
she was acting so as to advance
a mutual criminal conspiracy.

33:46.894 --> 33:48.417
- You would have to charge her.

33:48.461 --> 33:51.812
- I've charged her with being
an unindicted co-conspirator.

33:53.901 --> 33:57.122
Their communications
are no longer protected.

33:57.165 --> 33:59.602
Very clever.

33:59.646 --> 34:01.517
Mrs. Conway can testify.

34:01.561 --> 34:03.041
- Your Honor.

34:05.086 --> 34:07.088
And what did you see,
Mrs. Conway?

34:07.132 --> 34:10.874
- Sam rushing to sit up
in his bed.

34:10.918 --> 34:14.008
His face was white
as a ghost.

34:14.052 --> 34:16.750
There were tears
running down his cheeks.

34:18.752 --> 34:24.932
- My husband...
was standing over the bed.

34:26.803 --> 34:29.806
It looked like
he was fastening his belt.

34:33.375 --> 34:39.816
- Later, in bed, he told me
not to tell anyone what I saw.

34:43.864 --> 34:46.562
- Hmm.

34:46.606 --> 34:49.261
That's a story,
Mrs. Conway.

34:49.304 --> 34:50.566
- It's true.

34:50.610 --> 34:51.828
- Did you tell it to the nurse

34:51.872 --> 34:53.221
when you were called
to school?

34:53.265 --> 34:54.744
- No.

34:54.788 --> 34:56.572
- No.

34:56.616 --> 34:58.531
- To the police, the first time
you spoke with them?

34:58.574 --> 35:00.924
- It all happened so quickly.
I needed time.

35:00.968 --> 35:02.622
- To formulate
such a convincing tale.

35:02.665 --> 35:04.189
- Object--
- Withdrawn.

35:04.232 --> 35:07.409
Did you tell this story
to the police

35:07.453 --> 35:09.324
the first time
that you spoke to them?

35:13.459 --> 35:15.330
- No.

35:17.202 --> 35:19.247
- I just wanted it to go away.

35:19.291 --> 35:24.339
- Did you tell them
the second time you saw them,

35:24.383 --> 35:26.298
Mrs. Conway?

35:30.998 --> 35:33.305
No.

35:33.348 --> 35:38.658
- In fact, you never told
the police that John raped Sam,

35:38.701 --> 35:39.963
right?

35:43.750 --> 35:45.621
- I just told them
what I saw.

35:45.665 --> 35:50.974
- So you don't know what
actually happened in that room?

35:51.018 --> 35:52.846
No.

35:54.543 --> 35:56.850
- Thank you.

35:59.896 --> 36:01.376
- I love her,
I--I do,

36:01.420 --> 36:03.291
but sometimes, my mom,
she just--

36:03.335 --> 36:05.032
she doesn't know
what she's saying.

36:05.075 --> 36:06.816
Me and Dad,
we were just talking.

36:07.991 --> 36:09.993
- He was--
I don't know.

36:10.037 --> 36:11.865
He was just trying
to console me.

36:11.908 --> 36:13.954
You know,
I-I was feeling bad

36:13.997 --> 36:16.043
'cause I couldn't
shoot this rabbit,

36:16.086 --> 36:18.524
and, um, and he was just
telling me that it's okay,

36:18.567 --> 36:21.962
that some guys just
aren't cut out for hunting.

36:22.005 --> 36:24.051
- Hmm.

36:25.531 --> 36:27.576
Did he assault you, Sam?

36:29.274 --> 36:32.059
- No, no, that's--
that's ridiculous.

36:32.102 --> 36:34.409
- So how did you
get the injuries

36:34.453 --> 36:39.545
that Mr. Stone
has repeatedly called

36:39.588 --> 36:42.330
indications of rape?

36:45.812 --> 36:47.640
Do I have to?

36:47.683 --> 36:51.121
Yeah, you do.

36:54.299 --> 36:59.391
- Um, so I met a man.

37:01.262 --> 37:05.962
And...it was the first time.

37:06.006 --> 37:08.138
I-I-I wanted him to,
you know.

37:08.182 --> 37:11.533
It wasn't rape
or anything like that.

37:11.577 --> 37:14.580
- Thank you.

37:20.716 --> 37:21.891
What was that guy's name?

37:21.935 --> 37:24.503
- Um, I don't remember.

37:24.546 --> 37:25.852
- That's odd.

37:25.895 --> 37:27.549
Your first time, I think
you'd remember everything.

37:27.593 --> 37:30.683
- Well, nobody cares
what you think, Counselor.

37:32.511 --> 37:34.252
Sustained.

37:35.557 --> 37:37.864
- Tell me about
the hunting trip.

37:39.126 --> 37:40.258
- Whatever you remember.

37:40.301 --> 37:41.563
- Well, I remember it all.

37:41.607 --> 37:44.871
- Right, because
it was your first time.

37:44.914 --> 37:47.090
The first time you went out
in the woods with your dad,

37:47.134 --> 37:48.178
your brother, and a rifle.

37:48.222 --> 37:49.876
It was a big deal,

37:49.919 --> 37:51.312
kind of like the first time
you had sex.

37:51.356 --> 37:52.574
- Objection.
- My point is--

37:52.618 --> 37:54.228
the witness
remembers everything

37:54.272 --> 37:55.577
about his first hunting trip

37:55.621 --> 37:57.144
and nothing about
the first time he had sex,

37:57.187 --> 37:58.188
and they happened
on the same weekend.

37:59.973 --> 38:02.367
Everyone's making it out
to be something that it's not.

38:02.410 --> 38:04.325
I-it's just sex.
Everyone does it.

38:04.369 --> 38:05.718
- Not with their father,
they don't.

38:05.761 --> 38:07.110
- Objection!

38:07.154 --> 38:08.286
- That's not just sex, Sam.
It's rape.

38:08.329 --> 38:10.462
- Your Honor.
- That's enough.

38:10.505 --> 38:12.246
Mr. Stone.

38:12.290 --> 38:14.988
- Was going hunting
with your dad a big deal?

38:16.076 --> 38:18.339
- To Dad, it was.

38:19.862 --> 38:21.560
- But not to you.

38:23.518 --> 38:29.045
- Well...Dad killed a moose
when he was 12.

38:29.089 --> 38:31.091
Brian killed a deer
when he was 15.

38:31.134 --> 38:34.312
- In your family,
it's a rite of passage.

38:34.355 --> 38:36.357
- Yeah, it's how
you become a man.

38:36.401 --> 38:40.187
- How did you feel before
you tried to shoot the rabbit?

38:40.230 --> 38:42.624
In that moment
when time stands still

38:42.668 --> 38:46.498
and it was just you,
the rabbit, and your rifle?

38:46.541 --> 38:48.587
- Um...

38:48.630 --> 38:49.936
I--I don't--I don't know.

38:52.286 --> 38:54.636
Yeah, maybe, a little.

38:56.029 --> 38:57.726
- No, no, of course not.

38:58.771 --> 39:01.339
Were you scared of Brian?

39:05.691 --> 39:09.129
There was only one other
person there, Sam.

39:11.087 --> 39:13.351
Were you scared
of your dad?

39:17.529 --> 39:22.490
He put that rifle
in your hand, didn't he?

39:24.100 --> 39:25.667
You wanted
to make him proud.

39:25.711 --> 39:28.278
Isn't that right?

39:28.322 --> 39:30.237
There's no need
to be embarrassed.

39:30.280 --> 39:33.371
That's all any son wants.

39:33.414 --> 39:36.199
I just wanted to be a man.

39:38.550 --> 39:39.986
- I guess.

39:40.029 --> 39:42.597
- But you were scared.

39:42.641 --> 39:47.428
A man who gets scared is hardly
a man, isn't that right?

39:47.472 --> 39:51.476
A man who gets scared,
a boy who gets scared,

39:51.519 --> 39:54.043
he's a fraud.

39:54.087 --> 39:58.352
He needs to be punished,
be humiliated.

39:58.396 --> 40:00.441
And that's why your father
raped you, right?

40:00.485 --> 40:02.530
- Objection.
- Overruled.

40:02.574 --> 40:05.794
- No, no, no!

40:05.838 --> 40:07.056
My father would never do--

40:07.100 --> 40:08.580
my father would never do that.

40:08.623 --> 40:10.451
He would never.

40:21.419 --> 40:24.247
- Has the jury
reached a verdict?

40:24.291 --> 40:26.902
- We have, Your Honor.

40:28.338 --> 40:29.731
- On the sole count

40:29.775 --> 40:32.604
of the indictment of rape
in the first degree,

40:32.647 --> 40:36.390
we find the defendant
not guilty.

40:41.351 --> 40:48.576
♪
